		<div id="siteNotice"><script type='text/javascript'>if (wgNotice != '') document.writeln(wgNotice);</script></div>		<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading">Jean Meslier</h1>
		<div id="bodyContent">
			<h3 id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</h3>
			<div id="contentSub"></div>
									<div id="jump-to-nav">Jump to: <a href="#column-one">navigation</a>, <a href="#searchInput">search</a></div>			<!-- start content -->
			<p><b>Jean Meslier</b> (1664 – 1729), was a <a href="/wiki/Catholic" title="Catholic">Catholic</a> <a href="/wiki/Priest" title="Priest">priest</a> who was discovered, upon his death, to have written a book-length philosophical essay promoting <a href="/wiki/Atheism" title="Atheism">atheism</a>. Described by the <a href="/wiki/Author" title="Author">author</a> as his "testament" to his parishioners, the text denounces all <a href="/wiki/Religion" title="Religion">religion</a>, and argues the superiority of atheist <a href="/wiki/Morality" title="Morality">morality</a>.</p>
<div class="thumb tright">
<div class="thumbinner" style="width:252px;"><a href="/wiki/File:Meslier.jpg" class="image" title="Jean Meslier"><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/27/Meslier.jpg/250px-Meslier.jpg" width="250" height="290" border="0" class="thumbimage" /></a>
<div class="thumbcaption">
<div class="magnify"><a href="/wiki/File:Meslier.jpg" class="internal" title="Enlarge"><img src="/skins-1.5/common/images/magnify-clip.png" width="15" height="11" alt="" /></a></div>
Jean Meslier</div>
</div>
</div>
